ory can be of an antitheoretical nature, and whether moral metaphysics is still possible in this postmodern and postmetaphysical age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEthicszChina. 0aNeo-Confucianism. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Confucianism. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Ethics.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845292040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438452920423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438452920/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles